                        <%# Using guide-card class - ensure styles are in style.css %>
                            <div class="guide-card general">
                                <%# Added modifier class %>
                                    <div class="head"><i class='bx bx-info-circle'></i>
                                        <%# Icon for general info %>
                                            <h2>General Principles</h2>
                                    </div>
                                    <p>Proper waste segregation is crucial for recycling and composting efforts.</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><strong>Clean & Dry:</strong>Ensure recyclable materials (paper, plastic, cans) are clean and dry.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Empty Containers:</strong>Empty food and liquid containers before recycling.</li>
                                        <li><strong>Check Local Rules:</strong>Always refer to specific local guidelines as rules can vary.</li>
                                        <li><strong>When in Doubt,
            Throw it Out:</strong>If unsure if an item is recyclable or compostable, put it in general waste to avoid contaminating batches.</li>
                                    </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="guide-card compost">
                                <div class="head"><i class='bx bxs-leaf'></i>
                                    <%# Icon for compost %>
                                        <h2>Compostable (Organic Waste)</h2>
                                </div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Fruit and vegetable scraps (peels, cores, cuttings)</li>
                                    <li>Coffee grounds and paper filters</li>
                                    <li>Tea bags (check for plastic/staples)</li>
                                    <li>Eggshells</li>
                                    <li>Spoiled leftovers (<b>no meat, dairy, or oily foods</b> - check local rules)</li>
                                    <li>Paper napkins and towels (if not heavily soiled with chemicals)</li>
                                    <li><b>DO NOT Compost:</b>Meat, bones, dairy, fats/oils, diseased plants, plastic-coated items.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="guide-card recycle">
                                <div class="head"><i class='bx bx-recycle'></i>
                                    <%# Icon for recycle %>
                                        <h2>Recyclable</h2>
                                </div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><b>Paper:</b>Newspapers, magazines, cardboard (flattened), office paper, junk mail.</li>
                                    <li><b>Plastics:</b>Check for recycling symbols (numbers 1-7). Typically includes bottles (drinks, shampoo), jugs (milk), tubs (yogurt - check locally), some containers. Rinse clean.</li>
                                    <li><b>Glass:</b>Bottles and jars (clear, brown, green). Rinse clean. Remove lids (recycle separately if metal).</li>
                                    <li><b>Metal:</b>Aluminum cans (soda, beer), steel/tin cans (food). Rinse clean.</li>
                                    <li><b>DO NOT Recycle:</b>Plastic bags/film (check store drop-off), styrofoam, ceramics, broken glass, greasy pizza boxes, food-soiled paper, disposable coffee cups (usually mixed materials).</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="guide-card landfill">
                                <div class="head"><i class='bx bxs-trash'></i>
                                    <%# Icon for landfill/general waste %>
                                        <h2>General Waste (Landfill)</h2>
                                </div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Items that cannot be composted or recycled.</li>
                                    <li>Plastic wrap, film, bags (unless specific local recycling exists).</li>
                                    <li>Styrofoam packaging.</li>
                                    <li>Food-soiled containers (unless specifically accepted for composting).</li>
                                    <li>Broken ceramics or glass.</li>
                                    <li>Disposable diapers.</li>
                                    <li>Anything you are unsure about.</li>
                                </ul>
